4 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code § 21-6-403(a), concerning the uniform filing
5 fees to be charged by the clerks of court, is amended to read as follows:
6 (a)(1) The uniform filing fees to be charged by the clerks of the
7 circuit courts for initiating or reopening a cause of action in the circuit
8 courts in the state shall be as prescribed in this section.
9 (2) A revival of an outstanding judgment under § 16-65-501 shall
10 not be charged a reopening fee under subdivision (a)(1) of this section.
11 (3) No portion of the filing fees shall be refunded.
